fix: address fresh-context audit findings

A fresh-context audit agent ran read-only against the repo and returned
~30 issues across 3 severities. This commit addresses all CRITICAL, all
MAJOR, and most MINOR. Smoke test grew to 45 assertions covering the
new behaviour.

CRITICAL

* LICENSE was truncated (17 lines). Replaced with full Apache-2.0 text
  (202 lines) — the 17-line version failed compliance.
* docs/install.md FTS5 preflight always printed "FTS5 ok" even on builds
  without FTS5 (grep -qv on empty input exits 0). Replaced with CREATE
  VIRTUAL TABLE which is what install.sh already used correctly.
* User-global hooks (memory-session-start, memory-pre-compact,
  check-orphan-dashboards) shipped but were NEVER registered in
  ~/.claude/settings.json — three README-promised features silently
  did not run. Added user-harness/settings.json and taught install.sh
  to merge it (Python stdlib JSON-aware merge; dedupes by command
  string so re-installs don't double-register).

MAJOR

* budget.py `reset project` wiped every project's counters because the
  LIKE pattern was `project:%`. Scoped to the current project/session.
* Portable sha256: compute_clean_hash.sh and dry_run_gate.sh tried
  `shasum` (BSD/Perl) which is absent on minimal Linux. Fall-through to
  sha256sum → shasum → python hashlib.
* stuck-detector's alternating-cycle detector was hardcoded period-2.
  Now detects periods 2, 3, and 4 (ABAB, ABCABC, ABCDABCD).
* SQL injection hygiene: correction-detect.sh, learn-capture.sh,
  deadend-capture.sh, and notify.sh all built SQL via string
  interpolation with `'` escaping only. Moved to sqlite3 parameter
  bindings. Matters most for notify.sh ($NTFY_ID comes from the
  ntfy server response) and the two capture hooks (assistant-generated
  text). Smoke test includes an injection-attempt assertion.
* AppleScript injection in notify.sh: `sed 's/"/\\"/g'` doesn't escape
  $, `, or \. Switched to `osascript` heredoc reading values from
  env vars via `system attribute` — AppleScript never sees the text
  via string interpolation.
* Stage truth-source consolidation: stage.py had 4 valid stages,
  journal.py had 6 (different set). journal.py now imports stage.py's
  VALID_STAGES and adds 'debug' + 'improve' as search-policy sub-modes.
* calibration.py docstring showed dashed flags (--add, --close) that
  don't match the subcommand CLI (add / close). Fixed.
* clean/SKILL.md invoked audit.py via `bash` but audit.py is Python.
  Changed to `python3`.
* doc-guard.sh: moved rotate_hook_log call to AFTER the fast-path .md
  filter, so the vast majority of Write/Edit hits (source files) don't
  pay the rotate-log IO.
* scheduled-notes SKILL.md used `stat -f %m` (BSD-only). Replaced with
  portable mtime helper that tries `stat -c %Y` (GNU) first.
* zcm.sh anomaly regex narrowed: "Killed" now requires line-start
  anchor so "Killed the zombie process" mid-log doesn't false-fire.
  NaN is word-boundary-anchored.
* install.sh non-interactive handling: new --yes flag, --project-only
  for CI, auto-yes when stdin is not a TTY. --help added.

MINOR

* Scrubbed "matrix-thinking" and "learned-representations" leaks from
  docs/STARS.md and skills/clean/SKILL.md.
* autopilot.conf.example added — documents every variable and notes
  that the conf is shell-sourced (not parsed), so don't put untrusted
  content in it.
* ARCHITECTURE.md now explicitly explains the workflow.db vs memory.db
  split and why they aren't synchronized (roadmap: a promote.py bridge).
* install.sh schema-upgrade message no longer claims to do column
  migrations — it only applies CREATE IF NOT EXISTS additions.
* compute_clean_hash.sh guards against empty blob-hash (skip file
  instead of including a blank line in the hash input).
* Dead `import subprocess` removed from capture hooks (SQL moved to
  sqlite3 bindings; no longer needed).

NEW TESTS (smoke went 40 → 45 assertions)

* stuck-detector: 10 Read calls on different files stays silent.
* stuck-detector: 3-cycle ABCABC pattern detected.
* budget reset project: other project's counters untouched.
* [LEARN] parameterized insert: adversarial quote/SQL safely stored.
* installer settings merge: preserves pre-existing hooks, adds idastone
  hooks, idempotent across repeated installs.

